{"key":"processedPost-6757970","value":{"id":6757970,"first":6754221,"last":6758107,"when":1175976261,"utime":"04/07/07 11:04 PM","content":"I use about 10% verm to fluff up the substrate and hold a bit of water.  Gypsum is mostly calcium.  That's why it's used.  The other main ingredient in gypsum is sulphur, which lowers pH to keep the calcium from raising it too much.  That's why gypsum works well without swinging the pH too much either direction.","title":"Re: Using gypsum in bulk sub"}}